d 'SYNDATAKIT': module to generate synthetic econometric and financial data
d
d	syndatakit calls the syndatakit Python package to generate
d synthetic tabular data calibrated to	  the statistical
d properties of real econometric and financial datasets.  Generated
d data preserves    marginal distributions, Spearman rank
d correlations, VAR(1) temporal dynamics, and GARCH    volatility
d structure.  It contains zero real individuals and requires no
d data use agreements.	  Eighteen built-in profiles cover
d macroeconomic indicators (FRED), mortgage origination (HMDA),   
d bank call reports (FDIC), equity returns, corporate bonds,
d insurance, real estate, tax	 statistics, and commodity markets.
d  Each profile is calibrated against published aggregate   
d statistics from U.S. federal agencies and international
d statistical bodies.	 Fidelity scores range from 81.7% (IRS SOI,
d limited by extreme income tail) to 95.0% (CFTC, FDIC).    The
d fidelity score combines marginal moment agreement (45%), KS
d distributional fit (30%), and    Spearman correlation distance
d (25%). 
d
d KW: synthetic data
d KW: reproducibility
d
d Requires: Stata version 16 and syndatakit Python package
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260315
d
d Author: Nitya Hapani, NA
d Support: email  nitya@@syndatakit.com
d
